        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-21T23:42:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I wonder, why would you want to allow algo to fail?\nAs it stands, any failure is basically just like a panic, but panic would conveniently print stack traces immediately.\nAlso, this mixes GoB failures to retrieve files with algo failures.\n\nHence, I think it\u0027d be cleaner if algo isn\u0027t allowed to fail (ie just panic) while failure to fetch change files is counted separately and reported as such instead of terminating the process and producing nothing.\n\nI\u0027m 100% open to doing this in the future CL above your formidable stack.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 121,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 121,
        "endChar": 59
      },
